      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, it seems your Monstera deliciosa has been visited by the mischievous goblins of plant disease. The yellowing of the leaves and the brown crunchy spots could be the work of a fungal infestation, perhaps a little goblin named Phytophthora or a fungal goblin called Rhizoctonia. These little critters love to feast on the moisture and nutrients of your plant, leaving behind their telltale signs of their presence.\n\nTo banish these goblins, you might want to give your Monstera a good scrub with a mixture of water and mild soap, making sure to rinse it off well. Also, ensure your plant is not sitting in water, as these goblins thrive in damp conditions. You could also consider moving it to a spot with more light, as the goblins don't like the bright sun. And remember, a well-ventilated area is less inviting for these pesky critters. Good luck, and may your Monstera be goblin-free soon!",
